            <div class="bio-content">
                <h2>Michael Stevens, IAR</h2>
                <p class="text-lg text-accent">Investment Adviser Representative & Founder</p>
                
                <p>Michael Stevens didn't start his career planning to become a financial advisor. Originally on a pre-med track, his path changed dramatically when his father passed away during his college years. This life-changing event shifted his perspective and ultimately led him to the world of finance, where he discovered his passion for helping families navigate complex financial decisions.</p>
                
                <p>After completing his BS in Business Management at Utah Valley University, Michael earned his Series 66 certification and began building what would become Capital Wealth Advisors in 2010. His commitment to the fiduciary standard means he is legally obligated to act in his clients' best interests at all times - no conflicts, no commissions, just honest advice.</p>
                
                <p>Michael holds a California insurance license (#0G96805) and serves on the board of Junior Achievement of Utah, where he helps educate young people about financial literacy and entrepreneurship. This community involvement reflects his belief that financial education should be accessible to everyone.</p>
                
                <div class="bio-credentials">
